âœ… Step 1: Update your CSS (vehicle-estimate.css)

Add this at the bottom of your vehicle-estimate.css:

.vehicle-form-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); /* 3 columns */
    gap: 16px; /* space between columns */
    margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.vehicle-form-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
}

.vehicle-form-group.vehicle-double-width {
    grid-column: span 2; /* make description field span 2 cols */
}


ðŸ‘‰ If youâ€™d prefer 2 columns, just change:

grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);

âœ… Step 2: No Razor/HTML changes needed

Your _VehPopUp.cshtml markup is already grouped nicely:

<div class="vehicle-form-row">
    <div class="vehicle-form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.Make, "Make")
        @Html.EditorFor(m => m.Make, "ComboBoxEditor")
    </div>

    <div class="vehicle-form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.VehModel, "Model")
        @Html.EditorFor(m => m.VehModel, "ComboBoxEditor")
    </div>

    <div class="vehicle-form-group">
        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.Year, "Year")
        @(Html.Kendo().NumericTextBox()...)
    </div>
</div>


That grid CSS will automatically line them up side by side in 2 or 3 columns.

âœ… Step 3: Optional â€” widen popup

If you want breathing room for 3 columns, tweak your Index.cshtml popup init:

$("#estimatePopup").kendoWindow({
    modal: true,
    width: 1200,  // was 1150
    height: "auto",
    resizable: false,
    scrollable: false,
    title: "Estimate",
    visible: false,
    actions: ["Close"]
});

